<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416280>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Somatic morphology of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. specimen in vivo; B. alcohol-preserved specimen. Scale bar: 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416280/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416283>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Morphological characters of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. Head and anterior part of body, anterior view, arrow indicates the presence of ectoparasitic fungi, order Entomophthorales; B. same, lateral view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. same, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, dorsal view; F. same, lateral view, arrows indicate the dorsal tooth of epiproct; G. cross-section of a midbody ring, caudal view. Scale bars: A–D, 0.5 mm; E–F, 0.2 mm; G, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416283/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416285>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Morphological characters of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. anterior part of body, dorsal view; B. same, lateral view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. same, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, dorsal view; F. same, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, 1 mm; E–F, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416285/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416289>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Morphological characters of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. tip of antenna; B. mandibular gnathal lobe, anterior view; C. vulvae, caudal view; D. cross-section of a midbody ring, caudal view; E. limbus; F. same, zoom-in. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.3 mm; D, 1 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F, 0.004 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416289/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416287>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Male of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. gnathochilarium, ventral view; B. legs I, caudal view; C. legs II, caudal view; D. leg III, caudal view; E. leg VI, caudal view; F. leg VII, caudal view; G. midbody leg, caudal view; H. same, claw. Abbreviations: cs, coxosternum; csp, coxosternal process; cx, coxa; p, penis; t, telopodite. Scale bars: A–G, 0.2 mm; H, 0.05 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416287/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416292>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. anterior gonopods, caudal view; B. posterior gonopods, caudal view; C. microsetae at base of telopodites of anterior gonopods; D. flagellum of posterior gonopods; E. microsetae at lateral margin of posterior gonopods. Abbreviations: c, coxite; cp, coxite process; f, flagellum; l, lamelliform lobe; t, telopodite. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.01 mm; D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.02 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416292/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416294>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Microhabitat of Glyphiulus formosus (Pocock, 1895). A. typical deciduous forest habitat of G. formosus. B. flipped stone in same habitat. Arrow indicates one G. formosus revealed from under the stone." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4416294/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

